Description: Fragment of double handle from a Koan pottery transport amphora. Clay medium, purplish brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and unclear symbol.
Curator's comments: Probably drawn by Petrie (Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 59, 27), although he gives iota at the end rather than the very clear E.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0145)
